{"lemma":"أُسٌّ","slug":"أُسٌّ","root":"#.س.س","root_slug":"_-س-س","root_link":"/words/roots/_-س-س","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n715","n716","n717","n797","n810"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A3%D9%8F%D8%B3%D9%8C%D9%91"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"foundation, groundwork, basis"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"power, exponent"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"remain, relic, trace, vestige, mark left","tags":["Classical"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Related words include Aramaic אוּשָּׁא (ʾūšā, “foundation”) as well as Akkadian 𒀳 (uššu, “foundation”), Akkadian 𒁼 (išdu, “base, foundation, root”), Akkadian 𒆠𒆗 (sassu, “base, floor”), Hebrew יְסוֹד (yəsōḏ, “foundation”), Aramaic אִיסָדָא (ʾĕsāḏā, “thing placed beneath, at the base or bottom; pillow”), Sabaean 𐩱𐩯 (ʾs³, “foundation”), Arabic اِسْت (ist), أَسَاس (ʔasās), سُدَّة (sudda) and وِسَادَة (wisāda, “pillow”). The verb Arabic أَسَّسَ (ʔassasa) and its reflexive Arabic تَأَسَّسَ (taʔassasa) are likely denominals of this noun, itself likely also borrowed wholly or semantically from the Aramaic.\nCompare the verbs Arabic شَيَّدَ (šayyada, “to establish firmly, build high”) and Hebrew שָׁת (šāṯ, “to place, lay down, put down”), as well as Arabic شَدَّ (šadda, “to strengthen, make firm, make strong”)."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n715","headword_ar":"اَسٌّ","root":"As","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see what next follows, in six places."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n716","headword_ar":"اُسٌّ","root":"As","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"foundation, basis,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lowest part,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, Mgh, Msb, K,) of a building, (S, A, K,) or of a wall; (Mgh, Msb;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^as~N","text_ar":"اَسٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_is~N","text_ar":"اـِسٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asaAsN","text_ar":"اَسَاسٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, Mgh, Msb, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asasN","text_ar":"اَسَسٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) which is a contraction of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asaAsN","text_ar":"اَسَاسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"commencement"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a building: and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"any commencement"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a thing; as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^as~N","text_ar":"اَسٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asaAsN","text_ar":"اَسَاسٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asasN","text_ar":"اَسَسٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (M:) and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"origin, source, stock,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"root,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSol","text_ar":"اَصْل"},{"kind":"text","text":",) of a man; as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^as~N","text_ar":"اَسٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": or of anything; (M, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^as~N","text_ar":"اَسٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_is~N","text_ar":"اـِسٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asiysN","text_ar":"اَسِيسٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"heart"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a man; because [the Arabs believe that] it is the first thing that comes into existence in the womb: (M, K:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=saAsN","text_ar":"ا=سَاسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, Mgh, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_isaAsN","text_ar":"اـِسَاسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ususN","text_ar":"اُسُسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M, Mgh, Msb, K;) the first of which is pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^Ns~N","text_ar":"اٌسٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Mgh, Msb,) like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aqofaAlN","text_ar":"اَقْفَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qufolN","text_ar":"قُفْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Msb;) or of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asasN","text_ar":"اَسَسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asobaAbN","text_ar":"اَسْبَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sababN","text_ar":"سَبَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S;) or, as some say, of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ususN","text_ar":"اُسُسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEonaAqN","text_ar":"اَعْنَاقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EunuqN","text_ar":"عُنُقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] so that it is a pl. pl.; (TA;) and the second, of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^as~N","text_ar":"اَسٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EisaAsN","text_ar":"عِسَاسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eus~N","text_ar":"عُسٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Msb;) and the third, of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asaAsN","text_ar":"اَسَاسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Mgh, Msb,) like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EunuqN","text_ar":"عُنُقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EanaAqN","text_ar":"عَنَاقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^aw~ali","text_ar":"الاَوَّلِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"banaY bayotahu EalaY A^asaAsihi","text_ar":"بَنَى بَيْتَهُ عَلَى اَسَاسِهِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He built his house upon its first foundation."},{"kind":"text","text":"] (A.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qalaEahu mino A^us~ihi","text_ar":"قَلَعَهُ مِنْ اُسِّهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He uprooted it from its foundation"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amorihi Alka*ibu","text_ar":"اَمْرِهِ الكَذِبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN A^asaAsu","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ اَسَاسُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one, the foundation of his affair,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"case, is falsehood"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A, TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaAna *`laka EalaY A^us~i Ald~ahori","text_ar":"كَانَ ذٰلَكَ عَلَى اُسِّ الدَّهْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, A, K,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asihi","text_ar":"اَسِهِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_isihi","text_ar":"اـِسِهِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, K,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"That was in old,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ancient, time;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"at the beginning of time;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, * K;) and in like manner,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ealay A@soti","text_ar":"عَلَي ا@سْتِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ald~ahori","text_ar":"الدَّهْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (A.) ―         -b2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A remain, relic, trace, vestige, sign, mark,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"track,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of anything. (K.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xu*o A^us~a AlT~ariyqi","text_ar":"خُذْ اُسَّ الطَّرِيقِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlT~ariyqi","text_ar":"الطَّرِيقِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^as~a","text_ar":"اَسَّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", [accord. to different copies of the K, meaning,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Take thou to the track of the way,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] when one guides himself by any mark or track, or by camels' dung: but when the way is manifest, you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xu*o $araka AlT~ariyqi","text_ar":"خُذْ شَرَكَ الطَّرِيقِ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^us~N","text_ar":"اُسٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"remains of ashes"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"between the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^avaAfiY","text_ar":"اَثَافِى"},{"kind":"text","text":", q.v.: (M:) occurring in a verse of En-Nábighah Edh-Dhubyánee; but accord. to most relates of this verse, it is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=sN","text_ar":"ا=سٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","A","Mgh","Msb","K","M"]},{"entry_id":"n717","headword_ar":"اـِسٌّ","root":"As","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^us~N","text_ar":"اُسٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in several places."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n797","headword_ar":"اَسٍ","root":"Asw","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asowaAnu","text_ar":"اَسْوَانُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n810","headword_ar":"اَسٍ","root":"AsY","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", [agreeably with analogy, as part. n. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asiYa","text_ar":"اَسِىَ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] (M,) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=sK","text_ar":"ا=سٍ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asiY~N","text_ar":"اَسِىٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asoyaAnu","text_ar":"اَسْيَانُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K,) a dial. var. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asowaAnu","text_ar":"اَسْوَانُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA, [see art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Asw","text_ar":"اسو"},{"kind":"text","text":"])"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Grieving, mourning,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sorrowful:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, Msb, K:) fem. [of the first, or second,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asiyapN","text_ar":"اَسِيَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=siyapN","text_ar":"ا=سِيَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) and [of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AsyAn","text_ar":"اسيان"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asoyaAnapN","text_ar":"اَسْيَانَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asayoY","text_ar":"اَسَيْى"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) pl. [of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AsyAn","text_ar":"اسيان"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asoyaAnuwna","text_ar":"اَسْيَانُونَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asaAyuwna","text_ar":"اَسَايُونَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which is extr. and somewhat doubtful] (K) and [of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AsyAnp","text_ar":"اسيانة"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asoyaAnaAtN","text_ar":"اَسْيَانَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and [of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AsyY","text_ar":"اسيى"},{"kind":"text","text":"or of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asiyapN","text_ar":"اَسِيَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asaAyaA","text_ar":"اَسَايَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K) and [of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AsyY","text_ar":"اسيى"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asoyayaAtN","text_ar":"اَسْيَيَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.)"}],"source_refs":["M","K","Msb","TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}